&lt;H4&gt;Including Links in Chatterbox Messages&lt;/h4&gt;

See &quot;[id://43037]&quot;, which explains how to formulate various kinds of shortcuts
you can use for linking to things.  These shortcuts work in chatterbox messages
as well as in nodes.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Also see &quot;[id://17544]&quot; for additional info on how HTML is handled in general by the chatterbox.


&lt;!-- 2004-01-22 [jdporter] The following may still be true, but why bother?

&lt;P&gt;In [id://17534|private messaging], you have an additional means of linking that is available &lt;i&gt;only&lt;/i&gt; here; it is not supported in regular posts or in the public chatterbox.
&lt;br/&gt;
You can link to a node by its node ID number, using the syntax &lt;code&gt;[node_id=NNN]&lt;/code&gt;.
&lt;br/&gt;
For example, if you send &lt;code&gt;/msg vroom [node_id=131]&lt;/code&gt;, [vroom] will receive
a message with [The Monastery Gates] in his message inbox.

--&gt;

